PN,35302
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F353A1783521458
OL,3,CPolitician resigns from committee with
OL,4,Cscathing statement
OL,6,FIn a statement, the politician said
OL,7,Fthat "walking away is not something I
OL,8,Fdo lightly" and she had come to the
OL,9,Fdecision over an extended period of
OL,10,Ftime.
OL,12,FShe wrote that Deputy Kasantseva-
OL,13,FMiller's leadership is "autocratic
OL,14,Frather than collaborative" and
OL,15,F"independent thought is too often
OL,16,Ftreated as an inconvenience rather
OL,17,Fthan an asset".
OL,1,W~+$z5~{4~k4~k4~sj5  hws         G2/5
OL,2,W+.!/*%/*%/*%/*%+,"-$ /(,'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BCh Is News CThis Day FReg TV
FL,354,350,120,260,000,100
PN,35303
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F353A1783521458
OL,3,CPolitician resigns from committee with
OL,4,Cscathing statement
OL,6,FDeputy Camp continued that she "was
OL,7,Fnot elected to blindly follow a
OL,8,FPresident's agenda" and she did not
OL,9,Fwant "simply to endorse conclusions
OL,10,Fthat have already been reached".
OL,12,FShe added: "None of this should be
OL,13,Fmistaken for an unwillingness to
OL,14,Fundertake difficult work. Quite the
OL,15,Fopposite. I have never been afraid of
OL,16,Fdifficult work.
OL,18,F"I have only ever been concerned by
OL,19,Fenvironments where difficult questions
OL,20,Fare no longer welcome."
OL,1,W~+$z5~{4~k4~k4~sj5  hws         G3/5
OL,2,W+.!/*%/*%/*%/*%+,"-$ /(,'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BCh Is News CThis Day FReg TV
FL,354,350,120,260,000,100
PN,35304
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F353A1783521458
OL,3,CPolitician resigns from committee with
OL,4,Cscathing statement
OL,6,FIn response, Deputy Kasantseva-Miller
OL,7,Fhas rejected those claims.
OL,9,FIn a statement, she explained that
OL,10,Fdiscussions are "necessarily robust"
OL,11,Fand this is "a normal feature of
OL,12,Fconsensus government".
OL,14,FShe went on to say that "the public
OL,15,Frightly expects us to focus our time
OL,16,Fand energy on serving the island and
OL,17,Fdelivering results, rather than on
OL,18,Fpersonality politics".
OL,1,W~+$z5~{4~k4~k4~sj5  hws         G4/5
OL,2,W+.!/*%/*%/*%/*%+,"-$ /(,'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,
